  - **F-RB-1-c** — k_cat / K_M Eigen-Hammes ceiling distinguishes
    RIBOZYME from non-catalytic RNA aptamers (ceiling ≤ 10⁹
    M⁻¹s⁻¹ binding-only). Audit = aptamer null-control corpus n≥10.
  - **F-RB-3-diffusion-limit** — measured k_cat/K_M ≤ 10⁹ M⁻¹s⁻¹
    across all corpus members + simulated MVPs. Audit = registry
    aggregate over F-RB-2 30 rows + F-RB-4 sim row (deadline
    2026-09-28, co-runs with F-RB-2 closure).
  - **F-RB-3-b** — diffusion margin ≥ 1 order-of-magnitude in MVP
    (currently 4.08 orders, PASS). Audit = sim-row direct read.
  - **F-RB-3-c** — Mg²⁺ dependence sweep (1 / 5 / 10 / 25 mM)
    preserves Eigen-Hammes margin. Audit = MVP sim parameterised
    sweep, deferred to cycle 26 if not already in registry.

## Cycle 26 candidate gates

Items promoted from §STALLED audit (2026-05-06) to formal cycle-26
candidates; deadlines TBD at cycle-26 kickoff.

- **G26-RB-1** — F-RB-2 inter-rater reliability follow-up. Cycle-25
  audit returned `log_bf=79.74` 30/30 perfect (suspicious-perfect,
  scoring-rubric subjectivity flagged in `raw_91_c3_disclose`).
  Gate: ≥ 2 independent reviewers re-score corpus catalytic-core nt
  count + reaction-state-ladder mapping; require Cohen's κ ≥ 0.7
  inter-rater agreement to upgrade σ(6)=12 from STRUCTURAL-EXACT-
  CANDIDATE to STRUCTURAL-EXACT.
- **G26-RB-2** — J₂=24 quotient L4 reduction (24× speedup) decision.
  Currently DANGLING ("deferred to stretch" in C0b row). Either
  (a) implement single-pose → 24-pose quotient symmetry-reduction
  in `ribozyme_kinetics_simulation.py` and re-run sim with
  measured speedup, or (b) explicit demote: declare L4 reduction
  out-of-scope for hexa-bio v1.x, redirect to n6-architecture
  group-theory side. Decision deadline: cycle-26 kickoff.

